<br>
VT was end game, Emp Ssra was end game, PoP zones in my experience are just new zones for high levels to group and solo in. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=yamp>Yamp</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 128<br> <font color=#333333>(12/11/02 4:36:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm47.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_mad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: no</span><hr size=1> So far, there are two spots in the game where I've found soloing at level 65 to be efficient.<br>
<br>
1) Druid mobs in Plane of Storms; hunt in the zone-in or jungle area, send the 61 air pet, cast Malosini/a, then chain-cast Firebolt of Tallon.<br>
<br>
2) Nettling wraiths in Plane of Nightmares; hunt at the dock / hobgoblin area, send the epic pet, cast Malosini/a, then chain-cast Black Steel and Planar Renewal.<br>
<br>
Anything tougher than a nettling wraith is really dicey. I can keep my pet up by chain-casting Transon's Elemental Renewal and Planar Renewal, but then I can't keep that up for long before I go OOM.<br>
<br>
On to less pertinent stuff:<br>
<br>
I tried going to Halls of Honor to solo, but it didn't work; mobs hit for 508.  I can't aggro kite with no snare spell, especially since the spell that I use to build aggro has a 6+ second casting time.  I can't root-nuke with an earth pet because the mobs are level 61, too high for GVoc: Earth to root them.  I can't root it with a fire pet because the level 63 fire pet is too unreliable.<br>
<br>
I think it's unfair that they can be kited so easily, they don't summon and they're snareable.  I didn't mind the necros aggro-kiting them, but I felt kinda bad after I saw druids quadkiting there.  But hey, at least I'm not running away the whole time.  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>KITERS ARE PANSIES, LET IT BE KNOWN!</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
